<p>Portion of letter from Arthur Ferguson, 2.1916</p>
<p>Before closing I must relate a story told of one of our brigade's medical officers.</p>
<p>Well my good man, what's wrong with you?  Influenza?  Nasty thing influenza;  had it myself.  Take one of these &amp; two of those &amp; see me in the morning.</p>
<p>Well my good man what's wrong with you?  Constipation.  Nasty thing constipation, I've had it myself.  Take one of these &amp; two of those &amp; see me in the morning.</p>
<p>Well my good man, what's wrong with you?  Diarrhoea.  Nasty thing diarrhoea, I've had it myself.  Take one of these &amp; two of those &amp; see me in the morning.</p>
<p>Well my good man, what's wrong with you?  Gonorrhoea.  Nasty thing gonorrhoea, I've had it mys---  No I'm damned if I have.</p>
